 DISENGAGEMENT FROM GAZA AND ITS RAMIFICATIONS: The End of the Sharon Administration and the Ehud Olmert Administration (2005–2008) -- tChapter Eleven. CHANGES IN THE GREATER MIDDLE EAST: The Netanyahu Administration (2009–18) -- tChapter Twelve. ISRAEL’S COUNTERTERRORISM POLICY FROM THE PERSPECTIVE OF ISRAELI DECISION MAKERS -- tCONCLUSION. The Art of Israeli Counterterrorism -- tAPPENDIX -- tNOTES -- tSELECTED BIBLIOGRAPHY -- tINDEX0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aSince declaring independence in 1948, Israel has been involved in an intractable conflict with the Palestinians and its neighbors. While violence has ebbed and flowed over the years, the threat of terrorism has remained a constant factor, shaping Israeli security policy in a unique way.Boaz Ganor provides an authoritative analysis of Israel’s approach to counterterrorism throughout its existence. Drawing on unprecedented access to Israeli leaders, he offers a comprehensive insider’s account of the decision-making processes, challenges, and dilemmas at the core of counterterror activities. Beginning with infiltration attacks from neighboring states immediately after independence and proceeding through the formation of organized Palestinian terror organizations up to the present day, this book details distinct eras of terrorism and how the Israeli state has counteracted them. Ganor also highlights the dynamic nature of both terrorism and counterterrorism: Just as waves of terror rise, fall, and evolve, so too do the measures employed to respond to them. He distills the lessons of Israel’s experience into key tenets for other countries facing the challenge of terrorism.The book features revelatory personal testimony from senior Israeli decision makers who have played pivotal roles in counterterrorism strategy, including prime ministers, defense ministers, Israeli Defense Forces chiefs of staff, and directors of Mossad and Shin Bet. Israel’s Counterterrorism Strategy is indispensable reading for students, scholars, and practitioners alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aArab-Israeli conflict. 0aNational securityzIsrael. 0aPalestinian ArabsxPolitics and government. 0aTerrorismzIsraelxPrevention. 0aTerrorismzIsrael. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Middle Eastern.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073907708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021 Englishz978311075417908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021z9783110753943oZDB-23-PLW40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231553001423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231553001/original  a978-3-11-073907-7  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075417-9  EBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aZDB-23-PLWb2021